 goes undiscussed. Animated with evocative examples from scholarship, current events, and works of fiction, this framework presents a bold reimagining of organizational life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aOrganizational behavior. 0aSecrecyxSocial aspects. 4aBoundaries. 4aGroups. Identity. 4aInformal Secrecy. 4aOrganization Theory. 4aOrganizational Secrecy. 4aPublic Secrecy. 4aSecrecy. 4aState Secrecy. 4aTrade Secrecy. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Organizational Behavior.2bisacsh1 aCostas, Jana, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070397940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080479816740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804798167423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804798167.jpg  a978-3-11-070397-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles